abstract: As congressional candidates take a chance on changing districts, and even states, to try to get elected, they raise the question of whether local ties even matter anymore.

lead_paragraph: CHARLES TOWN, W.Va. — Only 30 miles and the Potomac River separate this bedroom community in the foothills of the Blue Ridge Mountains from Frederick, Maryland’s second-largest city.

abstract: Americans don’t trust government. Armed with data, a new generation of policy makers is trying to remedy that.
snippet: Americans don’t trust government. Armed with data, a new generation of policy makers is trying to remedy that.
lead_paragraph: If you wanted to bestow the grandiose title of “most successful organization in modern history,” you would struggle to find a more obviously worthy nominee than the federal government of the United States.

abstract: President Obama is having increasingly frequent late-night dinners, here and abroad, with companions from fields like architecture, film, art and literature.
snippet: President Obama is having increasingly frequent late-night dinners, here and abroad, with companions from fields like architecture, film, art and literature.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Obama had just disembarked from Air Force One and was still on the tarmac in Rome when he turned to his host, John R. Phillips, the American ambassador to Italy, with an unexpected request: How about a dinner party tomorrow night?
